{"timestamp": "2025-12-11 19:35:59.434278", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: **Network Diagnostic Report – Enterprise Hierarchical OSPF Network**\\n\\n| Item | Observation | Assessment |\\n|------|-------------|------------|\\n| **Host‑to‑Server Connectivity** | <ul><li>host_1_1_1_1 → web_server_0 (10.200.0.3): 3–4\\u202fms, 0\\u202f% loss</li><li>host_2_1_1_1 → web_server_0: 2–7\\u202fms, 0\\u202f% loss</li><li>host_1_1_1_1 → load_balancer (10.200.0.7): 3–5\\u202fms, 0\\u202f% loss</li><li>host_2_1_1_1 → load_balancer: 2–5\\u202fms, 0\\u202f% loss</li></ul> | **Healthy** – All end‑to‑end ICMP traffic to the web tier is low‑latency and loss‑free. OSPF routing between core, distribution, and server‑access routers is functioning correctly. |\\n| **DNS Server Latency** | host_1_1_1_1 → dns_server (10.200.0.2): ~1\\u202f000\\u202fms<br>host_2_1_1_1 → dns_server: ~1\\u202f000\\u202fms | **Anomaly** – DNS server is reachable but exhibits ~1\\u202fs round‑trip time, far higher than the ~3–5\\u202fms seen for other services. No packet loss is observed, so the path is intact but the DNS host is responding slowly. |\\n| **Other Network Checks** | No packet loss or significant jitter observed on any tested path. | **No other issues detected** – All tested links and routing entries appear correct. |\\n\\n### Summary of Findings\\n\\n1. **Routing & Connectivity** – The hierarchical OSPF topology is correctly advertising all subnets. Hosts can reach the web servers and load balancer with negligible latency, confirming that core‑to‑distribution and distribution‑to‑server‑access links are healthy.\\n\\n2. **DNS Performance** – The DNS server (10.200.0.2) is reachable but consistently returns ~1\\u202fs round‑trip times. This latency is an order of magnitude higher than other services and is likely due to the DNS host itself (CPU, memory, or configuration) rather than a network fault.\\n\\n3. **No Packet Loss** – All ping tests show 0\\u202f% loss, indicating that the physical and data‑link layers are functioning correctly.\\n\\n### Next Diagnostic Steps (if required)\\n\\n- Verify DNS server resource utilization (CPU, memory, disk I/O).\\n- Inspect DNS server logs for time‑outs or heavy query load.\\n- Confirm that the DNS server’s network interface is not experiencing congestion or mis‑configured MTU.\\n- Test DNS resolution from the hosts (e.g., `dig web0.local`) to confirm that the high latency is reflected in actual DNS queries.\\n\\n**Conclusion:** The network is otherwise healthy; the sole abnormal behavior is the high latency observed when contacting the DNS server. This points to a host‑side issue rather than a routing or link problem., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='a44e42c2-836a-40ed-891a-c0a83a9dc107'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "not_implemented", "id": ["langchain_ollama", "chat_models", "ChatOllama"], "repr": "ChatOllama(model='gpt-oss:20b', validate_model_on_init=True, temperature=0.0, base_url='http://10.68.186.140:11434')", "name": "ChatOllama"}}
